    <section name="Release Notes">
      <subsection name="5.0.0">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 11 June 2020</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href='https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPFORGE-252'>HIPFORGE-252</a><br/>
            Upgrade Hippo Utilities to 14.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="4.0.0">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 5 June 2020</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href='https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPFORGE-250'>HIPFORGE-250</a><br/>
            Upgrade to 13.4 and replace deprecated methods.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="3.1.1">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 25 May 2018</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href='https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPFORGE-131'>HIPFORGE-131</a><br/>
            New feature: a simple generic scheduler job to execute a Groovy script.
          </li>
          <li><a href='https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPFORGE-163'>HIPFORGE-163</a><br/>
            Fix for failed to deploy source jar due to duplicate maven-source-plugin effective
          </li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="3.0.0">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 3 August 2017</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Upgrade from log4j to log4j2 to be compatible with CMS 12.</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="2.0.1">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 13 Februari 2017</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPPLUG-1435">HIPPLUG-1435</a><br/>
            Fix <a href="hst/components.html">RedirectComponent</a> to not redirect twice.</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="2.0.0">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 17 August 2016</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPPLUG-1367">HIPPLUG-1367</a><br/>
            Upgrade Utilities to CMS 10 and CMS 11 compatible version</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="1.02.01">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 17 August 2016</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPPLUG-1365">HIPPLUG-1365</a><br/>
          Replace all deprecated methods and/or make parts deprecated that are not needed any more</li>
      </ul>
    </subsection>
      <subsection name="1.02.00">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 19 May 2014</p>
        <ul>
          <li>HIPPLUG-836: Upgrade to 7.9.</li>
          <li>Remove <a href="repository/scheduler-daemon.html">Scheduler Daemon</a>: similar functionality is
            <a href="http://www.onehippo.org/library/concepts/hippo-services/repository-scheduler.html">now available in Hippo Repository</a>.</li>
          <li>Remove Gallery Processor: the functionality is now available in Hippo CMS core.</li>
          <li>Upgrade and clean up dependencies.</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="1.01.03">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 13 May 2014</p>
        <ul>
          <li>HIPPLUG-571: administrative cleanup</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="1.01.02">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 5 September 2012</p>
        <ul>
          <li>HIPPLUG-338: skip terracotta autoupdate by setting a property in the Scheduler Daemon</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="1.01.01">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 6 April 2012</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Scheduler Daemon: added a mandatory properties file with activation flag
            'org.onehippo.forge.utilities.repository.scheduler.SchedulerDaemon.active', on behalf of clustered setup</li>
          <li>Scheduler Daemon: added BaseJob class providing access to JCR session and job configuration</li>
          <li>NodeUtils: moved from repository module (scheduler) to commons module</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="1.01.00">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 9 March 2012</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Initial release as a restructured version of old PSUtils forge project</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
    </section>
